name: lmbench

variants.name: build_system
variants.description: Build systems supported by the package

description:
lmbench is a suite of simple, portable, ANSI/C microbenchmarks for
UNIX/POSIX. In general, it measures two key features: latency and
bandwidth. lmbench is intended to give system developers insight into
basic costs of key operations.

dependencies.name: gmake
dependencies.description:
GNU Make is a tool which controls the generation of executables and
other non-source files of a program from the program's source files.

dependencies.name: libtirpc
dependencies.description: Libtirpc is a port of Suns Transport-Independent RPC library to Linux.
